## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| Two contexts (Stepper + StepperItem) | Avoids prop drilling for both global state (active value) and per-step state (completed, disabled) |
| No Radix UI primitive | No standard Radix stepper; pure React is cleaner and avoids dependency |
| Orientation via JS + data attributes | Context provides orientation to JS logic; `data-orientation` enables pure-CSS styling via group selectors (matches pattern in `tabs.tsx`) |
| `StepperContent` value is optional | Can be used inside `StepperItem` (inherits value) for vertical, or outside with explicit value for horizontal |
| Root is always `flex flex-col` | Stepper wraps both the step header area AND content panels; orientation affects `StepperItem`/`StepperSeparator` layout, not root |
| `useStepper` exported | Lets advanced users build custom sub-components or conditional rendering outside Stepper |

