# Plan: Stepper Compound Component for shadcn/ui

## Context

The codebase is a shadcn/ui monorepo. The primary app is at `apps/v4/`, which contains a registry system under `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/`. New components are added as `.tsx` files under `ui/`, demos under `examples/`, and each folder has a `_registry.ts` that lists all entries. The master registry aggregates all of these.

We need to add a `Stepper` compound component for multi-step wizards and onboarding flows — supporting horizontal and vertical orientations, React context-based state sharing, and all the sub-components the user requested. No existing stepper component exists, no conflicts.

**Constraint: Only create new files and add registry entries. Do NOT modify any existing component files beyond the two `_registry.ts` files.**

---

## Critical Files

| Path | Action |
|------|--------|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | **CREATE** — component implementation |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | **CREATE** — demo |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` | **MODIFY** — append entry before closing `]` |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` | **MODIFY** — append entry before closing `]` |

**Reference patterns from:**
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/carousel.tsx` — React context pattern (CarouselContext, useCarousel)
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/tabs.tsx` — orientation + data-* attribute CSS pattern
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/breadcrumb.tsx` — multi-export named component pattern
- `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/accordion-demo.tsx` — example file structure

---

## Step 1 — Create `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`

### Architecture

Two React contexts:
- **`StepperContext`** — shared by all sub-components: `{ value, onValueChange, orientation }`
- **`StepperItemContext`** — shared within a single step: `{ value, disabled, completed }`

Two custom hooks (both exported):
- `useStepper()` — reads `StepperContext`, throws if used outside `<Stepper />`
- `useStepperItem()` — reads `StepperItemContext`, throws if used outside `<StepperItem />`

### Sub-components and their Responsibilities

```
Stepper           Root container + StepperContext.Provider
StepperItem       Per-step wrapper + StepperItemContext.Provider
StepperTrigger    <button> that calls onValueChange(value)
StepperIndicator  Visual circle showing step number / checkmark / icon
StepperTitle      Step title <p>
StepperDescription Step description <p>
StepperSeparator  Line connector between steps (adapts to orientation)
StepperContent    Renders children only when step value matches active value
```

### Context Type Definitions

```ts
type StepperContextProps = {
  value: string
  onValueChange: (value: string) => void
  orientation: "horizontal" | "vertical"
}

type StepperItemContextProps = {
  value: string
  disabled: boolean
  completed: boolean
}
```

### `Stepper` component

```tsx
"use client"

import * as React from "react"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// ... (contexts, hooks) ...

function Stepper({
  value,
  onValueChange,
  orientation = "horizontal",
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & {
  value: string
  onValueChange: (value: string) => void
  orientation?: "horizontal" | "vertical"
}) {
  return (
    <StepperContext.Provider value={{ value, onValueChange, orientation }}>
      <div
        data-slot="stepper"
        data-orientation={orientation}
        className={cn("flex flex-col gap-4", className)}
        {...props}
      >
        {children}
      </div>
    </StepperContext.Provider>
  )
}
```

> The root is always `flex flex-col`. For horizontal mode, users wrap `StepperItem`s in a `flex flex-row` div (same pattern as Tabs where user controls inner layout).

### `StepperItem` component

```tsx
function StepperItem({
  value,
  disabled = false,
  completed = false,
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & {
  value: string
  disabled?: boolean
  completed?: boolean
}) {
  const { value: activeValue, orientation } = useStepper()
  const state = activeValue === value
    ? "active"
    : completed
    ? "completed"
    : "incomplete"

  return (
    <StepperItemContext.Provider value={{ value, disabled, completed }}>
      <div
        data-slot="stepper-item"
        data-state={state}
        data-disabled={disabled ? "" : undefined}
        data-orientation={orientation}
        className={cn(
          "group/stepper-item flex",
          orientation === "horizontal"
            ? "flex-row items-center flex-1"
            : "flex-col",
          className
        )}
        {...props}
      >
        {children}
      </div>
    </StepperItemContext.Provider>
  )
}
```

### `StepperTrigger` component

```tsx
function StepperTrigger({ className, children, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"button">) {
  const { onValueChange } = useStepper()
  const { value, disabled } = useStepperItem()

  return (
    <button
      data-slot="stepper-trigger"
      type="button"
      disabled={disabled}
      onClick={() => onValueChange(value)}
      className={cn(
        "inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-left text-sm",
        "disabled:pointer-events-none disabled:opacity-50",
        "focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}
```

### `StepperIndicator` component

Styled via parent `group/stepper-item` data attributes:

```tsx
function StepperIndicator({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"span">) {
  return (
    <span
      data-slot="stepper-indicator"
      className={cn(
        "flex size-8 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 text-xs font-semibold transition-colors",
        // incomplete
        "group-data-[state=incomplete]/stepper-item:border-border group-data-[state=incomplete]/stepper-item:text-muted-foreground",
        // active
        "group-data-[state=active]/stepper-item:border-primary group-data-[state=active]/stepper-item:text-primary",
        // completed
        "group-data-[state=completed]/stepper-item:border-primary group-data-[state=completed]/stepper-item:bg-primary group-data-[state=completed]/stepper-item:text-primary-foreground",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

### `StepperTitle` component

```tsx
function StepperTitle({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"p">) {
  return (
    <p
      data-slot="stepper-title"
      className={cn("text-sm font-medium leading-none", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

### `StepperDescription` component

```tsx
function StepperDescription({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"p">) {
  return (
    <p
      data-slot="stepper-description"
      className={cn("text-xs text-muted-foreground", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

### `StepperSeparator` component

Reads orientation from parent `group/stepper-item`'s `data-orientation` attribute via Tailwind group selectors:

```tsx
function StepperSeparator({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"div">) {
  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-separator"
      className={cn(
        "shrink-0 bg-border transition-colors",
        // completed: color the connector
        "group-data-[state=completed]/stepper-item:bg-primary",
        // horizontal: horizontal line that grows to fill item width
        "group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:h-px group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:flex-1 group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:min-w-8",
        // vertical: short vertical connector centered under indicator (size-8 = 32px, center = 16px = ms-4)
        "group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper-item:ms-4 group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper-item:mt-1 group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper-item:h-6 group-data-[orientation=vertical]/stepper-item:w-px",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

### `StepperContent` component

The `value` prop is optional — falls back to the enclosing `StepperItemContext` value (enabling placement inside `StepperItem` for vertical orientation without repeating the value):

```tsx
function StepperContent({
  value: valueProp,
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & { value?: string }) {
  const { value: activeValue } = useStepper()
  const itemCtx = React.useContext(StepperItemContext)

  const targetValue = valueProp ?? itemCtx?.value
  if (!targetValue || activeValue !== targetValue) return null

  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-content"
      className={cn("text-sm", className)}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

### Exports

```tsx
export {
  Stepper,
  StepperItem,
  StepperTrigger,
  StepperIndicator,
  StepperTitle,
  StepperDescription,
  StepperSeparator,
  StepperContent,
  useStepper,
}
```

---

## Step 2 — Create `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx`

### Design
- `"use client"` directive (uses `React.useState`)
- Imports: `CheckIcon` from `lucide-react`, `Button` from button ui, all 8 Stepper exports
- Shows **two demo sections**: horizontal wizard (primary) + vertical onboarding (secondary)
